# Frontend Conventions

## Component Location

Components are **never** co-located with the route that uses them. They always live in `src/components/<category>/`.

```
✅  src/components/auth/LoginForm.tsx
✅  src/components/profile/AvatarUpload.tsx
✅  src/components/ui/Button.tsx

❌  src/app/login/LoginForm.tsx
❌  src/app/dashboard/ProfileCard.tsx
```

Category matches the domain: auth components → `auth/`, profile components → `profile/`, shared primitives → `ui/`.

Each category folder has a barrel export:

```ts
// src/components/auth/index.ts
export * from "./LoginForm";
export * from "./SignupForm";
```

## Zod Type Files

All Zod schema files are named `.z.ts` so they're immediately identifiable:

```
✅  src/server/types/profile/index.ts  →  re-exports from profile.z.ts
✅  src/server/types/profile/profile.z.ts
✅  src/types/post/post.z.ts

❌  src/types/profileTypes.ts
❌  src/types/profile/schema.ts
```

The barrel `index.ts` re-exports from the `.z.ts` file — consumers always import from the index, never directly from the `.z.ts`.

## React Code Style

Sibling code blocks inside a component are separated by a blank line:

```tsx
// ✅
export function ProfileCard({ userId }: Props) {
  const [open, setOpen] = useState(false);

  const { data } = trpc.profile.me.useQuery();

  function handleSave() {
    setOpen(false);
  }

  return <div>{data?.username}</div>;
}

// ❌ — no blank lines between siblings
export function ProfileCard({ userId }: Props) {
  const [open, setOpen] = useState(false);
  const { data } = trpc.profile.me.useQuery();
  function handleSave() {
    setOpen(false);
  }
  return <div>{data?.username}</div>;
}
```

This applies to: hooks, derived values, event handlers, effects, and the return — each is its own visual block.
